<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="156" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="11.[148,373,882,903]" box="[148,373,882,903]" pageId="11" pageNumber="156">
<heading box="[148,373,882,903]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="11" pageNumber="156" reason="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[148,373,882,903]" pageId="11" pageNumber="156">
The 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Chaudoir" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[195,304,882,903]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saphyrinus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[195,304,882,903]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="156">saphyrinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[148,977,922,1262]" pageId="11" pageNumber="156">
Members of this group have the following character states: mentum with sides rounded, tooth not reaching apices of lobes, paramedian foveal pits small; lateral depressions of pronotum widely explanate posteriorly, partly with meshed microsculpture; disc of pronotum with indistinct meshed microsculpture; posterior angles of pronotum widely rounded; anterotransverse impression of pronotum widely indistinct medially; elytra without orange spot at apical fourth around suture; elytral microsculpture striate, lines indistinct; epipleuron with subapical plica; metasternum (laterally) and metepisternum with punctures; metasternum with shallow but distinct constriction medially at level of posterior edges of mesocoxae; tarsomeres 5 without setae underneath; endephallus with sclerotized ring; body size large (SBL 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[896,914,1162,1182]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="156">¼</emphasis>
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.23" metricValueMin="1.0699999999999998" pageId="11" pageNumber="156" unit="mm" value="11.5" valueMax="12.3" valueMin="10.7">10.7– 12.3 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="156" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[148,977,922,1262]" pageId="11" pageNumber="156">
This group includes a single, large, characteristic species, restricted to the southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[274,405,1241,1262]" name="United States of America" pageId="11" pageNumber="156">United States</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
